{
  "doc_id": "48775",
  "text": "Glucagon-like peptide-1 (GLP-1) has been demonstrated to affect the oxidative stress status in several in vitro [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , in vivo [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and clinical [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] studies. GLP-1 and its agonists are well known to improve glycemic control, decrease food intake, increase insulin release and increase insulin sensitivity which may contribute to reduced oxidative stress, but direct effects on reactive oxygen species (ROS) and antioxidant capacity have also been suggested to serve a role [CITATION_7] .",
